      "claim": "The congruence 7*n ≡ 23 (mod 50) has a unique solution modulo 50, and it is n ≡ 39 (mod 50).",
      "reasoning": "Since gcd(7,50)=1, 7 has a multiplicative inverse modulo 50. The inverse of 7 modulo 50 is 43 because 7*43=301≡1 (mod 50). Multiply both sides by 43: n ≡ 43*23 (mod 50). Compute 43*23 = 989 ≡ 39 (mod 50) because 989 = 19*50 + 39.",
      "facts_used": ["existence of modular inverse when gcd=1", "modular arithmetic"]
