    {
      "claim": "The set S = { n ∈ ℕ : n > 0 and n ≡ 39 (mod 50) }.",
      "reasoning": "From h₀, n ∈ S iff n > 0 and (14*n)%100=46. By steps 1-3, (14*n)%100=46 iff n ≡ 39 (mod 50). So S consists of positive integers congruent to 39 modulo 50.",
      "facts_used": ["step 1", "step 2", "step 3", "definition of S from h₀"]
